viders to work together. The authors present the benefits of such cooperation by reporting the findings of three qualitative research studies. Individuals in secular and sacral services who work with victims of domestic violence, as well as academics in the fields of social work, psychology, and religious studies, will benefit from the insights, depth of experience, and range of voices represented in this valuable book. Irene Sevcik, Michael Rothery, Nancy Nason-Clark, and The Very Rev. Robert Pynn have brought their professional expertise and experiences to benefit FaithLink at different times and in different capacities. All of the authors live in Calgary except Nason-Clark, who lives in Fredericton. Sponsored by The Calgary Foundation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aAbused wivesxServices for. 0aAbused womenxServices for. 0aChurch work with dysfunctional families. 0aFaith-based human services. 0aFamily violencexReligious aspects. 0aFemmes victimes de violencexServices. 0aPastorale des familles inadaptées. 0aReligion and culture. 0aServices sociaux basés sur la foi. 0aVictimes de violence familialexServices. 0aVictims of family violencexServices for. 0aViolence familialexAspect religieux. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Psychotherapy / Counseling.2bisacsh  aDomestic Violence.  aReligion.  aSocial Work.1 aNason-Clark, Nancy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPynn, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRothery, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311127402708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015z978311127703540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212065340uhttps://www.degruyter